# Block Element Behavior

See also [`BLOCK_RULES.md`](BLOCK_RULES.md) for foundational product rules.

## Block model

- Every individual element тАФ or any element that contains other elements тАФ is a **block**.
- Everything is made of **fundamental blocks** (primitives, variables, expressions, etc.) composed into larger blocks.
- **Function body** (Main Function / Function): tapping a **minimized chip** opens its **Block Editor** ([`BlockEditorPanel.tsx`](src/components/panels/BlockEditorPanel.tsx)).
- **Block editors** show the block's **full UI**; nested children stay **minimized chips**; tapping a chip opens **another** editor on the stack ([`editorStack`](src/App.tsx)). This repeats recursively.

## Core rules

- Start: **Main Function only** on canvas тЖТ [`emptyProgram.ts`](src/constants/emptyProgram.ts). Main cannot be deleted/nested.
- **Palette drops are slot-only.** Drag from the Blocks panel into a valid slot inside Main or an open block editor. Dropping on empty canvas does nothing.
- **Function** is not in the palette. Dropping a **Function Call** into a statement body auto-creates a linked Function definition (no canvas card; edit via block editor). Clicking a Function Call **mini chip** opens the linked **Function** block editor, not the call editor.
- Every slot needs `slotTarget` on [`BlockSlot.tsx`](src/components/ui/BlockSlot.tsx) or drag-drop is dead.
- Invalid drop тЖТ red dashed border + message. Never silent reject. Primitives auto-coerce to slot type on all typed value slot attaches.

## Blocks & nesting

**Tree:** Program = top-level canvas blocks ([`placements`](src/types/program.ts)) + nested children in parent `data` (body arrays, value slots, operands) тАФ CRUD in [`blockTree.ts`](src/lib/program/blockTree.ts).

| Context | Renders as | Where |
|---------|------------|-------|
| Top-level canvas | **Main only** тАФ full block + drag handle | [`CanvasBlocksLayer.tsx`](src/components/layout/CanvasBlocksLayer.tsx) |
| Editor panel root | Full block UI | [`BlockEditorPanel.tsx`](src/components/panels/BlockEditorPanel.tsx) тЖТ [`BlockRenderer`](src/components/canvas/BlockRenderer.tsx) |
| Any nested child (body, slot, editor) | **Minimized chip** (`nestedView: true`) | [`StatementBody.tsx`](src/components/blocks/StatementBody.tsx), slot blocks, [`BlockRenderer.tsx`](src/components/canvas/BlockRenderer.tsx) |
| `valueRef` | **ValueRefChip** (not minimized block) | [`BlockRenderer.tsx`](src/components/canvas/BlockRenderer.tsx) |

**`BlockRenderer` rule:** `nestedView && kind !== 'main'` тЖТ [`MinimizedBlockChip`](src/components/blocks/MinimizedBlockChip.tsx). Otherwise тЖТ full block component. Nested children default to `nestedView: true` in `renderChild`.

**Editor stack:** Click chip тЖТ `openBlockEditor` тЖТ [`BlockEditorPanel`](src/components/panels/BlockEditorPanel.tsx) (full UI for root only; nested children stay chips). Multiple editors stack ([`editorStack`](src/App.tsx)). Chip **├Ч** or panel remove тЖТ [`detachNestedBlock`](src/hooks/useEditorState.ts) (discards nested block).

**Never** render full nested block UI inline inside a parent тАФ chips only (except the single root block in an open editor).

## Where to drop (workflow)

| Step | Action | Block / slot |
|------|--------|--------------|
| 1 | Statement | Variable тЖТ `statement-body` |
| 2 | Value | Constant тЖТ Variable `variable-value` (not body) |
| 3 | Expression | Expression тЖТ body тЖТ editor тЖТ `expression-operand` left/right |
| 4 | Loops | For/While тЖТ body тЖТ editor тЖТ `for-init` / `for-condition` / `for-increment` / `while-condition` |

Containers grow vertically when a valid child is placed.

## Typed value matching

Value-producing blocks: **primitive**, **variable**, **expression**, **functionCall**, **valueRef**. Non-void function calls only; void calls are statements, not values.

- Per-kind semantics: [`blockContract.ts`](src/lib/program/blockContract.ts) тАФ `getBlockValueType`, `canUseAsStatement`, `canCreateValueReference`, `getMiniBlockView`.
- Slot attach rules: [`slotRules.ts`](src/lib/validation/slotRules.ts) тАФ `getSlotRequirement`, `canAttachBlockToSlot`, `canAttachPaletteKindToSlot`, `normalizeBlockForSlot`.
- Legacy wrappers: [`typeChecker.ts`](src/lib/validation/typeChecker.ts), scope helpers in [`scope.ts`](src/lib/program/scope.ts).
- Typed slots accept a block when `getBlockValueType(block) === expected` (via `canAttachBlockToSlot` / `canValueSlotAcceptBlock`). **Primitives** always fit typed value slots and coerce on attach (`normalizeBlockForSlot`).
- **Block drag** onto a value slot тЖТ nest/move the block (detach from old location via `attachBlockIdToSlot`).
- **Reference grip** / scope picker тЖТ `valueRef` only; source stays on its line (`assignReferenceToSlot`).

## Slot acceptance тЖТ [`slotRules.ts`](src/lib/validation/slotRules.ts)

| Slot | Accepts |
|------|---------|
| `statement-body` | variable, expression, print, functionCall, if, for, while тАФ **return** only inside functions; **not** primitive |
| `variable-value` | primitive, variable, expression, functionCall, valueRef тАФ type must match `valueType` (primitives coerce) |
| `print-value` | primitive, variable, expression, functionCall, valueRef (any value type) |
| `return-value` | primitive, variable, expression, valueRef тАФ type must match enclosing function `returnType`; unavailable for `void` |
| `if-condition` | boolean-valued blocks/refs |
| `expression-operand` | value nestable kinds тАФ match operand type (`getExpressionOperandType`; comparisons use **number** operands) |
| `for-init` / `for-increment` | number-valued blocks/refs (init: variable only; increment: expression only) |
| `for-condition` / `while-condition` | boolean-valued blocks/refs |
| `call-arg` | primitive, variable, expression, functionCall, valueRef тАФ type must match arg |
| `type-variable` | variable only |
| `function-signature` | type block only |

## In-scope refs

- Link keeps source on its line; consumer stores `valueRef`. **Use existingтАж** on empty slots (`scopeConsumerId`).
- Drag **ReferencePill** / link grip тЖТ value slot (not block drag). Usage edges in body ([`ConnectionLayer.tsx`](src/components/canvas/ConnectionLayer.tsx)). Source removal тЖТ error on ref.

